  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"alistar","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Alistar","Alistar","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Both of you spike at 2, but neither snaps the other: your Q (Hymn of Valor) double-cast pokes as Alistar walks up, while his W-Q (Headbutt into Pulverize) combo needs him to close distance first. Hold Power Chord and keep your ADC behind you so a flash-W engage doesn't catch you flat."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Alistar tips the fight the moment his R (Unbreakable Will) comes online; he becomes near-unkillable and dives your backline with W-Q, so your R (Crescendo) is the only hard answer. Save Crescendo to interrupt his W travel or to peel the instant he lands Pulverize on your carry, not to open."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still Alistar-favoured through the first item: a completed engage item plus boots lets him flash-headbutt through your zone and his ult negates your combo's burst. Track his flash and only step up to poke when it's down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Scaling flips to you (Sona) at two items: your aura stacking, Power Chord slows and teamfight Crescendo out-value a single-target engage tank once your carry is online."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke him down with E-empowered Q autos before he reaches Headbutt range","Keep your ADC spaced so W-Q can only ever catch one of you","Hold Crescendo to cancel his all-in or peel, never to initiate"],"foe":["Land W (Headbutt) into Q (Pulverize) to knock you up and burst","Flash-engage the moment your Crescendo or Flash is down","Use R to face-tank your combo and dive your carry"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a skill matchup: you out-poke with Hymn of Valor and Power Chord, but one clean Headbutt-Pulverize can flip a trade, so respect his all-in range and shield-song when he steps up.","mid":"Through levels 4-6 Alistar edges ahead: his W-Q engage and especially R make him the aggressor, and you must position defensively, wards on both flanks, Flash up, Crescendo saved to interrupt his dive rather than start fights.","late":"Once you hit two items the matchup swings to you; your persistent auras, slows and a wombo Crescendo outscale his single-target lockdown, so play patient in lane and cash in during grouped fights.","whys":["Level 1 is even because your Q poke and his empty engage range cancel out.","Level 2 is even: your Power Chord threat matches his first W-Q combo window.","Level 3 stays skill as your sustain-poke trades roughly with his short-cooldown engage.","Levels 4-5 remain even while his combo scales but your shielding keeps you safe.","Level 6 favours Alistar because Unbreakable Will lets him dive through your combo unkillable.","First item still favours Alistar as engage item plus flash out-ranges your peel.","2+ items favour Sona as your auras, slows and teamfight ult outscale a single-target tank."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"bard","win":["Bard","Bard","Bard","Bard","Skill","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Bard controls the early lane: his Q (Cosmic Binding) stuns you for a huge duration if it bounces off a minion or wall, and he pokes for free with autos empowered by Traveler's Call meeps. Your Q outranges nothing here, so sidestep his Q line and don't stand next to walls or the minion wall."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your first real equalizer: your R (Crescendo) is a reliable AoE stun while his R (Tempered Fate) is a skillshot that can accidentally save you or peel his own dive. Bait his Q, then Crescendo when he steps up so his roam-heavy playstyle can't punish you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Momentum shifts to Sona at the first item: your aura song stacking and Power Chord out-sustain his poke, and his lane pressure fades once he starts chunnel-roaming for portals. Punish his roam windows by shoving and poking his ADC 2v1."},{"when":"Late","text":"You (Sona) win the scaling war outright; persistent auras, empowered Power Chord slows and a teamfight Crescendo beat a pick-oriented Bard whose value is single stuns and utility."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Cosmic Binding by never lining up with a wall or minion","Match his roams by shoving and poking his ADC while he's gone","Save Crescendo to answer his engage once you hit 6"],"foe":["Land Q into a wall/minion for the long double stun","Poke with meep-empowered autos before you can retaliate","Roam through E (Magical Journey) portals to make plays elsewhere"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Bard: Cosmic Binding is a long-range stun that doubles up off walls and minions, and meep autos let him win the poke war, so play back, hug the center of the lane and only trade when his Q is on cooldown.","mid":"At level 6 things even out; your Crescendo matches his Tempered Fate as a fight-changer, and you can start punishing his roam timers by pushing and threatening his carry when he leaves.","late":"From the first item onward you take over, your aura sustain and slows outvalue his single stuns, and grouped fights let your Crescendo and Power Chord snowball a lead his utility kit can't match.","whys":["Level 1 favours Bard because Cosmic Binding threatens a long stun you can't answer.","Level 2 favours Bard as meep autos and Q out-trade your poke.","Level 3 stays Bard-favoured with his stun-poke pattern intact.","Levels 4-5 favour Bard while his roam pressure and Q dominate.","Level 6 is even as your Crescendo finally matches his Tempered Fate.","First item favours Sona as your aura sustain out-scales his fading poke.","2+ items favour Sona because persistent auras and teamfight ult beat pick utility."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"blitzcrank","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"The entire lane is decided by one thing: his Q (Rocket Grab). Land in his hook range and you or your ADC gets pulled into a Q-E-R combo that can delete you, dodge it and he's a near-useless stat-stick on cooldown. Stand behind minions at all times and hold Power Chord to punish the whiff."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Blitz's R (Static Field) adds burst and a silence to a landed hook, so a successful grab at 6 is often a kill. Your R (Crescendo) can't answer a hook mid-flight, so the counterplay stays positional, body-block the grab line for your carry and Crescendo him only after he commits E."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still a pure coin-flip on hooks: your first item improves your sustain and Power Chord chunk, but nothing about item timings changes the fundamental dodge-or-die dynamic. Keep vision on brushes so he can't grab from fog."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even into the late game the matchup is skill-gated; if you keep dodging grabs your auras and utility win, but a single late pull on your carry can still end a fight regardless of your lead."}],"wants":{"you":["Always keep a minion between you and Blitzcrank's hook line","Punish every whiffed Q with Power Chord and Hymn of Valor poke","Body-block grabs aimed at your ADC and ward flanking brushes"],"foe":["Land Rocket Grab to pull you into the Q-E-R burst combo","Grab from fog of war or fog-of-brush for a free pick","Silence with R after a hook so you can't Crescendo out"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are entirely about hook management: you out-sustain and out-poke a landed-nothing Blitzcrank, but one Rocket Grab flips a trade or ends a life, so hug minions, never facecheck brushes and threaten Power Chord when his Q is down.","mid":"Through 4-6 the dance is unchanged; respect his hook range on every wave, keep your carry spaced behind you, and remember his R silence makes a landed grab lethal, so vision denial and body-blocking are your real tools, not your combo.","late":"It stays a coin-flip into items; your scaling auras and slows are strong, but Blitzcrank never fully falls off because a single grab wins a fight, so the matchup is skill all game, dodge and you're ahead, get caught and you're behind.","whys":["Level 1 is skill because the lane hinges purely on dodging his hook.","Level 2 stays even: land Power Chord on a whiff or eat a grab, pure skill.","Level 3 is skill as the hook-or-punish dynamic is unchanged.","Levels 4-5 remain even, still decided by hook management.","Level 6 stays skill because his R makes a hook lethal but positioning still counters it.","First item is even as timings don't alter the dodge-or-die pattern.","2+ items stay skill since one late grab flips fights regardless of your lead."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"brand","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Brand","Brand","Brand","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Early it's an even poke war: your double-cast Q (Hymn of Valor) trades with his Q (Sear) and W (Pillar of Flame), but he can only stun you with Sear if you're already Ablaze from W. Stay unblazed by dodging his W circles and you neutralize his lockout, then poke back with E-empowered autos."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Brand pulls ahead here: his R (Pyroclasm) bounces for massive AoE damage in a 2v2 and his passive burns melt your low base health. Your Crescendo can start a fight but you'll lose the follow-up burn trade, so use R defensively to peel his all-in rather than to engage into his damage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still Brand-favoured once he completes a Lost Chapter item: his mana sustain lets him spam W-Q combos that out-DPS your sustain, and his passive stacks chunk you through shields. Play from max range and only step up when his Q is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Scaling flips to you (Sona) at two items; your aura stacking, Power Chord slows and utility Crescendo out-value a squishy immobile mage once fights spread out and your carry comes online."}],"wants":{"you":["Avoid W (Pillar of Flame) so you never get stunned by Sear","Poke with E-empowered Q autos when his Sear is down","Save Crescendo to peel his Pyroclasm all-in, not to open"],"foe":["Land W first to set up the guaranteed Q stun","Spam W-Q combos with mana sustain to out-poke you","Bounce R (Pyroclasm) between you and your ADC for AoE burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are an even poke duel: both of you chunk from range, but his stun only lands if you're Ablaze, so dodge his Pillar of Flame, deny the W-Q setup, and answer with your own Hymn of Valor poke.","mid":"From level 4 through 6 Brand takes over; his mana-sustained combo spam, passive burn and especially Pyroclasm out-damage your kit in the 2v2, so respect his range, ward for jungle collapses and hold Crescendo to disrupt his ult rather than trade into it.","late":"At two items the matchup swings back to you, your persistent auras, slows and teamfight utility outscale an immobile burst mage, so survive his mid-game spike and cash your advantage in grouped fights.","whys":["Level 1 is even because your poke trades with his and his stun needs a W setup.","Level 2 stays skill as Power Chord answers his combo when Sear is down.","Level 3 remains even with both sides chunking from range.","Levels 4-5 favour Brand as mana-sustained combo spam out-poke your sustain.","Level 6 favours Brand because Pyroclasm and passive burn out-damage you in the 2v2.","First item favours Brand as his sustained AoE out-DPS your kit.","2+ items favour Sona because auras, slows and utility outscale an immobile mage."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"braum","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Braum","Braum","Braum","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Even early: your Q poke chips Braum, but his passive (Concussive Blows) means if he lands Q (Winter's Bite) and then autos you four times you get stunned. Don't stand where he can weave autos after his Q, and punish him when his Winter's Bite is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Braum edges ahead here: his R (Glacial Fissure) is a knockup-line ult that starts fights or peels his carry through your engage, and his W (Stand Behind Me) plus E (Unbreakable) shield make him hard to burst. Your Crescendo can be soaked by his E-block angle, so time it around his cooldowns."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still Braum-favoured: his sustain-tank profile with a completed item lets him body-block your Power Chord and peel every poke you land onto his ADC. Poke him from angles his E shield isn't facing."},{"when":"Late","text":"You (Sona) win the long game; once you have two items your aura stacking, slows and a teamfight Crescendo out-value a single defensive tank whose kit is all peel and no scaling damage."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke Braum when Winter's Bite is down to avoid his passive stun","Angle Power Chord and autos away from his E (Unbreakable) shield","Save Crescendo to catch him when his E and R are on cooldown"],"foe":["Land Q then weave autos to trigger the Concussive Blows stun","Use E (Unbreakable) to block your poke and Power Chord","Start or peel fights with R (Glacial Fissure) knockup"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are even: you out-poke a Braum who can't reach you, but respect his passive, one Winter's Bite plus stacked autos stuns you, so trade when his Q is down and don't let him free-stack his passive on you or your ADC.","mid":"From level 4 through 6 Braum takes the edge; his shields, W-taunt peel and Glacial Fissure ult make him the sturdier presence and blunt your all-in, so play for poke, ward for jungle ganks and hold Crescendo for a window where his E is down.","late":"At two items the matchup flips to you, your persistent auras, slows and wombo Crescendo outscale a purely defensive tank, so grind out poke early and win the grouped fights once your carry is online.","whys":["Level 1 is even because your poke offsets his short engage range.","Level 2 stays skill as Power Chord answers him when Winter's Bite is down.","Level 3 remains even with careful poke around his passive.","Levels 4-5 favour Braum as his shields and peel blunt your trades.","Level 6 favours Braum because Glacial Fissure and E-block out-tank your combo.","First item favours Braum as his sustain-tank body-blocks your poke.","2+ items favour Sona because auras, slows and teamfight ult outscale a defensive tank."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"galio","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Galio","Galio","Galio","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Early it's even: your Q double-cast out-ranges his short poke, but his W (Shield of Durand) charges into a taunt and his passive on-hit magic damage punishes you if you stand next to him. Poke from max range and don't let him walk you down into E (Justice Punch) range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Galio spikes hard here: his R (Hero's Entrance) lets him or his mid roam in with a knockup shield, and his E-W combo (Justice Punch into taunt) locks you for a full burst. Your Crescendo answers the engage, but keep Flash up because his taunt plus ult chains CC through your combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still Galio-favoured: a completed item plus his W damage-reduction make him a durable engage threat who can flash-E onto your carry. Ward the flanks, respect his all-in range, and don't get caught in a taunt-into-ult chain."},{"when":"Late","text":"Scaling swings to you (Sona); at two items your aura stacking, Power Chord slows and teamfight Crescendo out-value a single-target engage tank once fights spread and your ADC is online."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke from max range so his W-charge and E can't reach you","Keep your ADC spaced so E-W taunt only catches one target","Save Crescendo and Flash for his E-W-R engage chain"],"foe":["Charge W then E (Justice Punch) into a taunt to lock you down","Chain taunt into R (Hero's Entrance) knockup for uninterruptible CC","Flash-E onto your carry when your Crescendo is down"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are even: you out-range his poke and can chip him freely, but his W taunt and E gap-close punish any misstep, so hold max distance, deny the walk-up, and trade with Hymn of Valor when his E is on cooldown.","mid":"From 4 through 6 Galio takes over; his W damage reduction, E-W taunt lock and Hero's Entrance make him a heavy engage threat that dives your backline, so ward wide, keep Flash and Crescendo ready to break his CC chain, and don't get isolated.","late":"At two items the matchup flips to you, your persistent auras, slows and wombo Crescendo outscale a single-target diver, so weather his mid-game and win the grouped teamfights once your carry comes online.","whys":["Level 1 is even because your range offsets his short-range engage.","Level 2 stays skill as your poke trades while his taunt is out of reach.","Level 3 remains even with disciplined max-range poke.","Levels 4-5 favour Galio as his taunt and W tankiness win extended trades.","Level 6 favours Galio because Hero's Entrance and E-W chain CC out-engage you.","First item favours Galio as his durable flash-engage threatens your carry.","2+ items favour Sona because auras, slows and teamfight ult outscale a single-target tank."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"hwei","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Hwei","Hwei","Hwei","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Both of you hit level 2 wanting the same thing: you with a second Hymn of Valor (Q) proc plus Power Chord, Hwei with QE (Devastating Fissure) to root. If Hwei blows QE on your ADC, punch forward with double Q and a melody-empowered auto for a clean chunk before his combo comes back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Hwei's level 6 is far scarier than yours: Ultimatum (R) is a massive AoE that sets up his own EQ/QW pokes and locks you for his ADC's follow-up. Crescendo is single-target and only really pays off inside a committed all-in, so respect his R zone and don't clump with your carry inside it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Hwei's first big AP item (Malignance/Blackfire Torch line) his EQ zone and QW bolt hit like a mid laner, out-ranging your Q poke and shredding you through the wave. Play from max range and only step up when his QW or EE (Pool of Reflection shield) is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your aura stacking (Q/W/E persistent auras) plus Crescendo teamfight lockdown scales past a squishy poke Hwei who has no reliable escape once his EW self-peel is used. Group, hold your R for his frontline commit, and your sustained AoE outvalues his single rotation."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge his QE root so he can't chain into QQ/QW burst","Stack aura auto-resets with Power Chord in the level 2/3 window","Reach 2 items where your teamfight R and healing outscale him"],"foe":["Land QE (Devastating Fissure) to root you or your ADC for his combo","Zone the wave with EQ/QW so you can't step up to poke or CS","Snowball his mid-game item spike where his pokes out-range your Q"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a skill matchup: your double-cast Q gives you the better instant poke-and-heal tempo, but Hwei's QW bolt and QE root can punish any greedy step, so trade in short bursts and use Power Chord to win the auto exchanges.","mid":"From level 4 through 6 Hwei tilts ahead — his zoning trifecta (QE root, EQ pool, QW bolt) plus his level 6 Ultimatum out-ranges and out-damages your single-target poke, so give ground, ward his flanks, and only contest when a key spell is down.","late":"Once you complete items your aura persistence and Crescendo swing it back: you enable your ADC through every fight while Hwei stays a fragile poke mage with no escape, so play for grouped teamfights where your R catches him and his squad.","whys":["Even early — your reset Q poke trades evenly against Hwei's slower QW/QE cast windows.","Even — the level 2 spike is symmetrical, decided by who lands their spell first.","Even — at level 3 both kits are online and neither reliably wins the short trade.","Hwei ahead — his EQ/QW/QE zoning locks you off the wave through levels 4-5.","Hwei ahead — Ultimatum's AoE zone and item-backed poke out-range your single-target R.","Hwei ahead — his first AP item makes his pokes hit harder and farther than your Q.","Sona ahead — two items in, your aura scaling and Crescendo teamfight control outvalue a squishy escape-less Hwei."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"janna","win":["Janna","Janna","Janna","Skill","Skill","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Janna's early lane is stronger than yours: her Zephyr (W) slow plus passive movement-speed lets her land free autos and disengage your Power Chord step. At level 2 she can also flash-Monsoon-independent tornado (Q) to interrupt any all-in you try, so don't over-commit expecting a kill."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Both ults are defensive-ish but yours is offensive lockdown while hers is pure reset — Monsoon (R) knocks your whole side back and heals her ADC, hard-countering a Crescendo all-in if she times it. Bait her R or force it early, because once it's down your Crescendo engage finally connects."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After your first item your aura poke (Q) and heal throughput start to out-sustain Janna's shield-and-peel kit, which brings little damage of its own. She wins the disengage war but not the poke war, so grind her ADC's HP with melody autos rather than chasing kills."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you out-scale a utility-only Janna: your persistent auras buff your whole team while her value caps at one Monsoon per fight. Group and force teamfights where your AoE speed/heal aura plus Crescendo overwhelm her single peel window."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait or track Janna's Monsoon before committing Crescendo","Out-sustain her with Q poke once your first item lands","Scale to grouped fights where your auras beat her pure utility"],"foe":["Use Zephyr slow and passive MS to win early auto trades","Hold Monsoon to hard-disengage your all-in and heal her carry","Peel her ADC through your poke with tornado interrupts"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Janna: her Zephyr slow, movement-speed passive and Tailwind let her out-position you and interrupt your Power Chord steps, so play safe, farm melody procs, and don't force trades you can't finish through her tornado.","mid":"By levels 4-6 it evens out — your poke-and-heal tempo matches her peel, and the fight hinges on skill: whether you can bait Monsoon before landing Crescendo, and whether she can time her R on your engage.","late":"Once items come online you pull ahead: Janna offers no damage and caps at one disengage per fight, while your stacking auras and Crescendo let you enable your ADC every skirmish, so group and play for teamfights.","whys":["Janna ahead — her Zephyr slow and MS passive win the level 1 poke and positioning battle.","Janna ahead — at level 2 her tornado interrupt shuts down your Power Chord all-in.","Janna ahead — level 3 she still out-trades you with slow-empowered autos and disengage.","Even — by levels 4-5 your poke tempo catches up to her peel, decided by execution.","Even — level 6 is a coinflip on whether Monsoon or Crescendo lands first.","Sona ahead — your first item makes your poke and heal out-sustain her damage-light kit.","Sona ahead — two items in, your team-wide auras outscale a pure-utility Janna."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"karma","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Karma","Karma","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Karma's threat is her early access to a slowing root: RQ isn't up yet at 2, but a raw Q (Inner Flame) that clips you sets up her ADC. Your level 2 double-Q plus Power Chord matches her poke, so trade back the instant her Q lands and misses, since it has a real cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Karma has no true ultimate spike — she gets Mantra at level 1, so 'level 6' just means her RQ (Inner Flame) poke is a big empowered nuke plus her RE (Defiance) shield-speed disengages your all-in. That empowered poke out-ranges your Q, so respect the RQ tether and don't sit in it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first AP item Karma's RQ poke hits like a burst mage and her RE shield negates your Crescendo commit, so this window favors her. Farm from range, use your heal aura to undo her chip, and don't let her free-cast Mantra Q onto you and your carry."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in your persistent auras and full Crescendo lockdown scale past Karma, whose Mantra value stays flat and whose shields can't cover a whole teamfight. Group up and force fights where your AoE stun catches her and her ADC together."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade back right after her Q or RQ poke goes on cooldown","Undo her chip damage with your heal aura and out-sustain","Reach 2 items where your auras and Crescendo outscale her Mantra"],"foe":["Land RQ (Inner Flame) empowered poke to out-range your Q","Use RE shield-speed to disengage your Crescendo all-in","Snowball the mid-game where her empowered poke out-damages you"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are an even skill matchup: your reset-Q poke-and-heal trades blow-for-blow with Karma's Q, and because she spends Mantra charges on poke or shields you can punish the cooldown windows — win the lane by trading right after her Q lands.","mid":"At levels 5-6 Karma edges ahead as her Mantra-empowered RQ becomes a long-range burst nuke and RE gives her a strong disengage against your engage, so give ground, poke from max range, and let your heal aura erase her chip.","late":"Once items complete you overtake her: your stacking speed/heal auras buff the whole team and Crescendo delivers a fight-winning AoE stun, while Karma's utility stays single-target and can't peel an entire teamfight, so play for grouped objectives.","whys":["Even — your double-Q poke trades evenly with Karma's Q in the level 1 exchange.","Even — the level 2 spike is symmetrical between reset-Q and her Q poke.","Even — level 3 both kits trade blow-for-blow around cooldowns.","Even — through levels 4-5 your poke-and-heal keeps pace with her Mantra usage.","Karma ahead — her Mantra-empowered RQ nuke out-ranges and out-damages your Q.","Karma ahead — first item makes her RQ burst and RE disengage beat your commit.","Sona ahead — two items in, your team-wide auras and Crescendo outscale her flat Mantra utility."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"leona","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Leona","Leona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Leona's whole game is landing Zenith Blade (E) into Shield of Daybreak (Q) stun; before level 6 she can't chain her full lockup, so level 2 is a real window for you. Stand behind minions so her E can't dash to you, and poke her with Q whenever she steps up to farm."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is Leona's kill spike: Solar Flare (R) plus E-Q-passive means point-and-click, unmissable lockdown that stuns you long enough for her ADC to delete your carry. You cannot out-heal being CC-chained, so hug your tower, ward the flanks, and never facecheck brush at level 6."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first tank/engage item Leona's all-in becomes very hard to survive — one E hook onto you or your ADC turns into a full stun chain plus her ADC's damage. Position so a minion is always between you and her E, and hold your slow/Power Chord to peel the moment she commits."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you finally out-scale: your speed aura kites her engage, your heal aura undoes her burst, and Crescendo can beat her to the punch or peel her off once she dives. Group with your team so she can't isolate you, and your sustained AoE wins protracted fights."}],"wants":{"you":["Stand behind minions so Leona's Zenith Blade (E) can't reach","Poke her with Q every time she steps up before level 6","Scale to items where your speed/heal auras kite her all-in"],"foe":["Land E-Q chain, then Solar Flare (R) at 6 for a full stun lock","Facecheck-punish or brush-flank to open her engage","All-in the moment her ADC can follow the CC chain"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are a skill matchup: Leona has strong base stats but can't fully lock you up before 6, so if you keep minions between you and her Zenith Blade and poke her with reset-Q, you win the farm-and-poke phase clean.","mid":"Levels 5-6 flip hard to Leona — Solar Flare turns her E-Q into an unmissable multi-second stun chain that your healing simply can't outlast, so play max-range, ward both flanks, and never get caught facechecking.","late":"Once your items come online you retake control: speed aura to kite her gap-close, heal aura to survive the initial burst, and Crescendo to either preempt or peel her engage — group tightly so she can't isolate you and your scaling wins.","whys":["Even — before her chain is online you trade evenly with poke and Leona relies on base stats.","Even — level 2 she still can't lock you fully; positioning behind minions keeps it skill.","Even — at level 3 her single stun is dodgeable and your Q poke matches her.","Even — through levels 4-5 you can still deny her engage with minion positioning.","Leona ahead — Solar Flare at 6 gives her an unmissable full stun-chain all-in.","Leona ahead — first item makes her E-Q-R lockdown lethal past your healing.","Sona ahead — two items in, your speed/heal auras and Crescendo kite and outscale her engage."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"lulu","win":["Lulu","Lulu","Lulu","Lulu","Skill","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Lulu wins the early exchanges: her Glitterlance (Q) slow plus a Pix-empowered auto out-pokes and out-trades your single Q, and her E (Help, Pix!) both shields and adds burst poke. Don't try to walk her down at 2 — she'll Q-slow you and kite your Power Chord step with ease."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Wild Growth (R) is a clutch anti-engage: it knocks you up if you dive and gives her ADC a huge health buff plus slow, hard-countering a Crescendo all-in. Force or bait her R before you commit, because until it's down your engage just gets peeled and punished."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After your first item the poke war starts to even and then tip your way: your reset-Q and heal aura out-sustain Lulu, whose damage is front-loaded and whose shields can't stop steady chip. Grind her carry's HP from range rather than forcing an all-in into her Polymorph."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you out-scale a single-target enchanter: your auras buff the whole team while Lulu's shield/knockup only ever save one ally. Group and play for teamfights where your AoE speed, heal and Crescendo stun overwhelm her one-target peel."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive to your first item where your poke out-sustains her","Bait Wild Growth (R) before committing Crescendo","Group for fights where your team-wide auras beat her single peel"],"foe":["Use Glitterlance slow and Pix to win every early trade","Polymorph you to cancel your combo and disengage","Hold Wild Growth to knock up and negate your all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Lulu: her Glitterlance slow, Pix-empowered autos and E shield-poke out-trade your single-target Q every time, and her Polymorph threat shuts down any Power Chord step, so play safe and just farm melody procs behind minions.","mid":"Level 5 evens as your poke-and-heal tempo catches up, but her level 6 Wild Growth is a strong anti-dive tool — the fight becomes skill, hinging on whether you bait her R before landing Crescendo.","late":"From your first item onward you pull ahead: your reset-Q out-sustains her front-loaded poke and your stacking auras buff the whole team, while Lulu's peel only ever protects one ally, so group and force AoE teamfights.","whys":["Lulu ahead — Glitterlance slow and Pix autos win the level 1 trade.","Lulu ahead — level 2 her Q-slow and E shield-poke out-trade your single Q.","Lulu ahead — level 3 Polymorph threat and superior poke keep her on top.","Lulu ahead — through levels 4-5 her kite-and-shield out-values your engage attempts.","Even — level 5/6 your poke tempo catches up and it comes down to baiting her R.","Sona ahead — your first item lets your reset-Q and heal out-sustain her front-loaded kit.","Sona ahead — two items in, your team-wide auras and Crescendo outscale a single-target Lulu."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"lux","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Lux","Lux","Lux","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Lux's whole threat is landing Light Binding (Q) — a 2-target root on a long cooldown. Before she snowballs, level 2 is even: dodge her Q by weaving behind minions and punish the ~12s cooldown window with your double-Q poke and a Power Chord step while her root is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Final Spark (R) turns a landed Q into a near-execute combo (Q-E-auto-R) that can delete your ADC from range, and it refreshes on takedowns. This is her big spike — never sit in a straight line with your carry, and treat every Lux Q as a potential setup for lethal follow-up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first AP item (Luden's/Malignance) Lux's Q-E-R poke chunks half your health bar and out-ranges your Q, so this window favors her hard. Farm from max distance, keep minions between you and her Q line, and use your heal aura to reset the chip she lands."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you out-scale a squishy poke Lux who has no escape: your persistent auras buff the team and Crescendo can flash-stun her out of position before she lands a Q. Group so she can't pick you, and if you get on top of her she has no way out."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Light Binding (Q) and punish its long cooldown window","Keep minions between you and her skillshot line","Reach 2 items where your auras and Crescendo catch an escape-less Lux"],"foe":["Land Q root to chain E-R burst on you or your ADC","Poke you down with Q-E and item-backed range","Snowball her mid-game where her burst out-ranges your Q"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are a skill matchup decided by her Q: if you respect Light Binding's long cooldown, dodge behind minions and punish the down-window, your reset-Q poke-and-heal keeps the lane even or better before she gets damage items.","mid":"From level 4 through 6 Lux tilts ahead — her Q-E poke and level 6 Final Spark, backed by her first AP item, out-range your Q and threaten to delete your carry off any landed root, so give ground and never line up with your ADC.","late":"Once items complete you overtake her: Lux is a squishy, escape-less poke mage, and your speed/heal auras plus a flash-Crescendo let you close the gap and lock her down before she can burst, so group and force fights where she can't safely poke.","whys":["Even — pre-items your reset-Q poke trades evenly with a dodgeable Lux Q.","Even — level 2 her long-cooldown root leaves clear windows to punish.","Even — level 3 you match her poke as long as you dodge Light Binding.","Lux ahead — from level 4 her Q-E poke out-ranges your Q as items come online.","Lux ahead — Final Spark at 6 turns any landed root into a lethal ranged combo.","Lux ahead — her first AP item makes the Q-E-R burst out-range and out-damage you.","Sona ahead — two items in, your auras and flash-Crescendo catch an escape-less poke Lux."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"maokai","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Maokai","Maokai","Maokai","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Rush Power Chord/Q for the level-2 shove and get your Hymn of Valor (Q) poke off before Maokai has both W-Q; if he saplings a bush you can trade the double aura and back off before his Bramble Smash (Q) roots the minion line into you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Nature's Grasp (R) is a long telegraphed wall-root that sets up a Twisted Advance (W) all-in with his ADC; hold Crescendo (R) as the counter-stun and never facecheck brush while his ult is up, because a landed R feeds his whole engage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first component and Aria of Perseverance (W) shields, you start soaking his sapling poke for free; Maokai's damage plateaus while your persistent auras and heal-shield keep your ADC topped through his zone control."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your Power Chord slows plus Crescendo turn his single-target W engage into a punished overextension; you out-sustain and out-teamfight him as long as you dodge the initial Twisted Advance."}],"wants":{"you":["Space just outside his W (Twisted Advance) lock-on range so his engage whiffs","Poke with Q on his approach and pre-shield your ADC before his sapling chunks land","Save Crescendo to cancel his R-into-W all-in"],"foe":["Land Nature's Grasp (R) wall to root you for a free Twisted Advance","Zone the wave with saplings so you can't Q-poke safely","Twisted Advance onto your ADC when your shield and R are down"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even skill: you have the stronger Q poke and level-2 tempo, but Maokai's saplings and Bramble Smash contest the wave and let him zone you off caster minions, so trade auras and don't get greedy into brush.","mid":"Levels 4-5 tilt to Maokai because his Twisted Advance (W) becomes a reliable point-and-click gap-close onto you or your ADC, and at 6 his Nature's Grasp wall threatens a long-range root that starts a coordinated 2v2 all-in he wins if it lands.","late":"By first item and beyond he keeps the edge through his engage threat, but once you hit two items your shields, heals, and Crescendo let you nullify his single-target lock-on, and by 2+ items you flip the matchup as your sustained enablement outscales his burst engage.","whys":["Level 1 is even: your Q out-ranges his sapling poke but his brush control offsets it.","Level 2 is even: you spike with Power Chord but Maokai matches with Bramble Smash wave zoning.","Level 3 is even: both have core abilities and neither can commit a clean all-in yet.","Levels 4-5 favour Maokai: Twisted Advance gives him a point-and-click engage you must respect.","Level 6 favours Maokai: Nature's Grasp wall-root sets up a 2v2 all-in that wins if it lands.","First item favours Maokai: his engage threat still dictates lane while your scaling isn't online yet.","2+ items favour Sona: your shields, heals, and Crescendo outvalue his single-target burst engage."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"milio","win":["Milio","Milio","Milio","Milio","Skill","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Milio's Ultra Mega Fire Kick (Q) is a knock-back bounce that can peel your engage and poke you first; his Warm Hugs (E) shield plus movement speed makes his ADC hard to punish early, so don't over-Q into a lane you can't force a kill in."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Breath of Life (R) is a team-wide cleanse-heal that undoes your Crescendo (R); bait his ult or wait it out, because ulting into a fresh Milio R just gets your chain-stun cleansed and your all-in wasted."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you hit your first item your Power Chord and Q burst start out-poking his shield uptime; Milio can't hard-engage, so you dictate the poke war and force him to spend E/R reactively."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, Crescendo forces his R early or catches multiple targets; your teamfight impact eclipses his single-layer peel once you can chunk through his shields and slows with Power Chord."}],"wants":{"you":["Win the extended poke war once your first item lands and your Q burst out-trades his shields","Bait or track his Breath of Life (R) before committing Crescendo","Force him to spend Warm Hugs (E) shields defensively so his ADC falls behind on tempo"],"foe":["Poke you with Ultra Mega Fire Kick (Q) and peel your approach with the knock-back","Keep his ADC shielded and speed-boosted to safely out-trade you early","Hold Breath of Life to cleanse your Crescendo and heal his team out of your all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 favour Milio: his Q poke, E shields, and passive fire-damage empowerment let him win the early poke war and keep his ADC safe, so you can't force favourable trades and should just soak XP and scale.","mid":"Level 5 is even skill as both of you hold ults and neither can hard-commit, then at 6 respect his Breath of Life (R) cleanse — but your first-item Q and Power Chord poke start clawing the lane back once his early shield advantage fades.","late":"By first item and especially 2+ items you flip it: Sona's aura stacking, Power Chord slows, and a well-timed Crescendo overwhelm Milio's single-layer peel, and he has no engage to punish your scaling.","whys":["Level 1 favours Milio: his Q poke and passive empowerment out-trade your early auras.","Level 2 favours Milio: E shields and speed keep his ADC safe from your Power Chord trade.","Level 3 favours Milio: his sustained poke and peel still dictate the lane.","Levels 4-5... Level 4 favours Milio: his shield and poke advantage persist before your items.","Level 5 is even: both hold ults and neither can force a decisive all-in.","First item favours Sona: your Q burst and Power Chord out-poke his shield uptime.","2+ items favour Sona: aura stacking and Crescendo outscale his single-layer peel."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"morgana","win":["Morgana","Morgana","Morgana","Morgana","Skill","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Morgana's Dark Binding (Q) is a 2.5s+ root on a long cooldown; her Tormented Shadow (W) puddle poke and Q threat let her control the lane, so hug minions and never walk in a straight line where a Q catches you into her ADC's follow-up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Soul Shackles (R) is a point-blank chain that stuns after a short delay — she'll flash-R or W-into-R for an all-in; hold Crescendo (R) to interrupt the shackle before it snaps, and pre-shield with Aria (W) to survive the tether."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once your poke and sustain come online you soak her W puddle for free and out-heal her chip; her Black Shield can block one Crescendo, so bait it with Q/Power Chord before you commit your ult."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your aura DPS and Power Chord slow outvalue her one-shot Q; if she misses Dark Binding she has no engage, and Crescendo out-teamfights her single Soul Shackles once you play around Black Shield."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Dark Binding (Q) by juking behind minions, then punish the long cooldown","Bait Black Shield with poke before committing Crescendo","Out-sustain her Tormented Shadow (W) poke once your first item lands"],"foe":["Land Dark Binding to root you or your ADC for a kill-setup","Zone the wave and poke with Tormented Shadow puddles","Flash Soul Shackles (R) for a point-blank chain-stun all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 favour Morgana: her Dark Binding root threat and Tormented Shadow poke let her dictate spacing, and a single landed Q into her ADC can kill you outright, so play safe behind the wave and respect the CC.","mid":"Level 5 is even as both hold ults, then at 6 her Soul Shackles all-in is real but counter-able — save Crescendo to break the chain and Black Shield only stops one target, so a disciplined trade neutralizes her engage while your scaling begins.","late":"By first item and 2+ items you take over: Sona's relentless aura poke, heals, and Power Chord slows out-sustain her skillshot-reliant kit, and if her Q misses she's helpless while your Crescendo dominates the fight.","whys":["Level 1 favours Morgana: her Q root threat and W poke control the lane spacing.","Level 2 favours Morgana: a landed Dark Binding into her ADC can kill you outright.","Level 3 favours Morgana: Tormented Shadow poke and root cooldown still dictate the lane.","Level 4 favours Morgana: her CC and poke advantage persist before your items come online.","Level 5 is even: both hold ults and neither can safely force the all-in.","First item favours Sona: your sustain and poke out-trade her chip once online.","2+ items favour Sona: aura DPS and Crescendo outscale her skillshot-reliant kit."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"nami","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Nami","Nami","Nami","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Nami's level-2 spike is real — Ebb and Flow (W) bounce-heal plus Aqua Prison (Q) bubble lets her set up a hard trade; don't clump with your ADC where her W can chain both of you, and dodge the slow-travel Q with a sidestep."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Tidal Wave (R) is a wide knock-up-and-slow that starts her ADC's all-in; hold Crescendo (R) as your counter and don't stand in a line, because an R into Q bubble chains enough CC to delete you or your carry."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Nami edges the poke war around first item because her W trades cost her nothing net (it heals back), while your Aria shields must out-value both her poke and her ADC's; play the long sustain game and don't lose the aura war."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you overtake her: your persistent aura DPS, Power Chord slow, and Crescendo out-scale her cooldown-gated bounce-heal, and in extended fights your uptime beats her burst-poke windows."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep Aqua Prison (Q) and refuse to line up for Ebb and Flow (W) bounces","Win the long sustain war with aura stacking once you out-scale her","Hold Crescendo to answer her Tidal Wave (R) engage"],"foe":["Land Aqua Prison bubble to lock you for her ADC's burst","Chain Ebb and Flow between you and your ADC for a value trade","Open with Tidal Wave (R) into Q to chain-CC a kill"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are even skill: both of you are poke-sustain supports trading auras, and while Nami has a strong level-2 bubble-into-W trade, you match her damage and neither wins without a misstep, so respect her Q and keep positions split.","mid":"Levels 4-6 favour Nami: her Ebb and Flow net-zero trades let her win the poke exchange, and at 6 her Tidal Wave gives her the stronger engage to open a coordinated 2v2, so play defensively and dodge her CC.","late":"By 2+ items Sona takes over: your uninterrupted aura DPS, Power Chord slows, and Crescendo out-scale Nami's cooldown-reliant bounce-heal, and in prolonged fights your uptime beats her burst windows.","whys":["Level 1 is even: both are poke-sustain supports trading auras with no edge.","Level 2 is even: Nami's bubble-W trade is strong but you match her aura damage.","Level 3 is even: neither can force a kill without the other missing a skillshot.","Levels 4-5 favour Nami: her net-zero Ebb and Flow trades win the poke war.","Level 6 favours Nami: Tidal Wave gives her the stronger 2v2 engage.","First item favours Nami: her cost-free W poke keeps her ahead in the sustain war.","2+ items favour Sona: aura DPS and Crescendo outscale her cooldown-gated heal."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"nautilus","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Nautilus","Nautilus","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Nautilus lives and dies by Dredge Line (Q) hook; the early levels are even because a missed Q leaves him on a long cooldown while you punish with Q poke, but never facecheck brush or stand behind a low minion he can hook through."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Depth Charge (R) is an unstoppable homing knock-up that chains with his Q and Titan's Wrath (W) shield-attack for a full lockdown; hold Crescendo (R) to peel the instant he R's your ADC, and Aria-shield the target before the chain lands."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Around first item Nautilus spikes hardest — his Q-E-R chain becomes a guaranteed kill if it connects, and his W shield tanks your poke; keep max distance, deny the hook, and only shield reactively so you don't feed his engage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you overtake him: if he can't land Dredge Line he has no engage, and your aura DPS, Power Chord slow, and Crescendo let you kite and out-teamfight his single hard-commit."}],"wants":{"you":["Deny Dredge Line (Q) by never facechecking brush or lining up behind minions","Punish his long hook cooldown with Q poke on every whiff","Save Crescendo to peel his Depth Charge (R) engage off your ADC"],"foe":["Land Dredge Line to pull himself in and start the CC chain","Chain Q into Depth Charge (R) for an unstoppable full lockdown","Use Titan's Wrath (W) shield to tank your poke and dive your ADC"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are even skill: Nautilus is entirely hook-reliant, so a dodged Dredge Line lets you punish his cooldown with Q poke, but one landed Q into his passive root and W can chunk your ADC hard — discipline decides these levels.","mid":"Levels 5-6 favour Nautilus: at 6 his Depth Charge unstoppable ult chains with Q and passive into a full lockdown that wins the 2v2 if it connects, and his W shield lets him tank your poke through the all-in.","late":"By 2+ items Sona flips it: Nautilus is a one-shot engage tool, so if the hook misses he's useless, and your aura DPS, Power Chord slows, and Crescendo let you kite his commit and dominate extended fights.","whys":["Level 1 is even: Nautilus is hook-reliant and a missed Q lets you punish freely.","Level 2 is even: neither can force a kill unless a Dredge Line lands.","Level 3 is even: his cooldown-gated hook keeps trades neutral.","Levels 4-5... Level 4 is even: still hook-dependent before his ult comes online.","Level 5-6 favours Nautilus: Depth Charge chains a full unstoppable lockdown that wins the all-in.","First item favours Nautilus: his Q-E-R chain becomes a guaranteed kill and W tanks your poke.","2+ items favour Sona: aura DPS and Crescendo outscale his single hard-commit engage."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"neeko","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Neeko's early poke with Blooming Burst (Q) and the tangle from Tangle-Barbs (E) out-ranges your comfortable Q range; don't clump with your ADC because her E root grows and passes through units, chaining you both into her burst."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pop Blossom (R) is a delayed AoE stun she'll flash or Passive-disguise into for a surprise 2v2 all-in; hold Crescendo (R) to interrupt her channel, and if you see her walk at you unarmed, expect a Flash-R and pre-shield."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Neeko keeps the edge around first item — her E root plus R burst can chunk or kill through your shields if you group up; stay spread, soak XP, and shield reactively rather than trying to win the poke war you lose."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you finally flip it: her damage is burst-and-disengage with no sustain, so your continuous aura DPS, heals, and Power Chord slows out-value her cooldown windows once you survive to scale."}],"wants":{"you":["Stay spread so Tangle-Barbs (E) can't chain-root you and your ADC","Interrupt Pop Blossom (R) channel with Crescendo","Survive to 2+ items where your sustain out-values her burst windows"],"foe":["Chain Tangle-Barbs root through minions into a Blooming Burst combo","Disguise with her passive and Flash into Pop Blossom (R) for a surprise stun","Win every early trade with superior poke range and burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 heavily favour Neeko: her Blooming Burst poke and growing Tangle-Barbs root out-range and out-damage your auras, so you cannot contest the poke war — hug XP range, stay spread, and give up CS rather than eat a root-into-burst.","mid":"Levels 5-6 still favour Neeko: at 6 her Pop Blossom flash-stun all-in threatens to delete your ADC, and her E-Q-R burst chunks through shields, so respect every unarmed approach and save Crescendo purely to break her channel.","late":"Only at 2+ items does Sona take over — this is why the win rate favours you overall despite a losing lane: Neeko has zero sustain, so your relentless aura DPS, heals, and Power Chord slows outscale her burst-and-hide kit once you survive the early game.","whys":["Level 1 favours Neeko: her Q poke and E root range out-trade your auras.","Level 2 favours Neeko: Tangle-Barbs chain-root into burst wins the trade.","Level 3 favours Neeko: superior poke and burst keep you zoned off CS.","Level 4 favours Neeko: her damage advantage persists before your items.","Level 5 favours Neeko: her burst combo still out-trades your early kit.","Level 6 favours Neeko: Pop Blossom flash-stun all-in can delete your ADC.","2+ items favour Sona: continuous sustain and aura DPS outscale her burst-and-hide kit."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"poppy","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Poppy","Poppy","Poppy","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Rush Power Chord: land Hymn of Valor (Q) twice into Poppy and her ADC to burn her out of Heroic Charge (E) range before she gets a wall to pin you against."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Poppy's Keeper's Verdict (R) can cancel your Crescendo, but your Aria of Perseverance (W) shield + heal lets you eat her E stun and still peel; hold R for after she blows charge."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Moonstone/Dawncore online your Power Chord Diminuendo and W sustain outheal Poppy's poke, and you can chain-slow her ADC in every skirmish."},{"when":"Late","text":"Crescendo into a grouped Poppy comp flips fights; her single-target E stops mattering while your AoE stun+auras carry teamfights."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait Poppy's Heroic Charge (E) with no wall behind you, then Power Chord slow her out","Keep W shields on your ADC so her E knockback engage fizzles","Stack auras and poke with Q so she can never trade back evenly"],"foe":["Pin you against a wall with E for the stun and burst you down","Land Keeper's Verdict to cancel your Crescendo in a fight","Punish your low base MS when you're caught out of position early"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are skill-driven: Poppy has no ranged poke, only Iron Ambassador (passive) shield pickups and a slow-ish Heroic Charge, so you match her by spacing Q pokes and never standing next to walls where her E stun becomes a kill threat. Don't over-extend into brush where she can E you into terrain; keep your ADC behind you and use Aria (W) to top off any chip. Trade with Q + Power Chord and back off before she closes the gap.","mid":"From level 4 into 6 Poppy edges ahead because her E all-in with W's Steadfast Presence slow zone lets her lock you or your ADC against a wall, and she out-durables your poke with her passive shields. Respect the wall geometry constantly and pre-shield with W when you see her step up. Ward the flanks so a jungler can't set up her E stun; if she commits E with no wall, she gets nothing.","late":"Once you finish your first support item and stack items, the matchup swings to you: Crescendo is a teamfight-winning AoE stun that dwarfs Poppy's single-target Heroic Charge, and your persistent auras plus W sustain keep your carry alive through her dives. Group up, deny her the isolated pick, and use Power Chord Diminuendo to cut her burst.","whys":["Level 1 is even: Poppy has no poke and you have no all-in, just passive positioning around walls.","Level 2 is a skill matchup; whoever spaces trades better wins, neither has a hard spike.","Level 3 stays even since Poppy still can't threaten a kill without wall setups you can avoid.","Levels 4-5 favor Poppy as her E-into-wall stun and shield sustain overpower your poke.","Level 6 favors Poppy because Keeper's Verdict can cancel your ult while her E all-in stays lethal near walls.","First item still favors Poppy; her durability and engage outweigh your item timing here.","2+ items favors Sona as Crescendo and stacked auras turn teamfights your way over her single-target kit."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"pyke","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Pyke","Pyke","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Q + Power Chord punishes Pyke hard when he steps up to melee CS, since he has low base health for a support and no shields to eat your poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Pyke's Death From Below (R) executes low targets and resets; your W heal + shield can lift your ADC just above the execute threshold, but respect his all-in windows."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Pyke spikes at level 6 with R + Phantom Undertow (E) stun chains; your Crescendo can interrupt his hook or channel if you hold it defensively."},{"when":"Late","text":"With items your auras and Crescendo peel a fed Pyke; deny his roam value by shoving and warding so he can't snowball off picks."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke Pyke with Q every time he approaches for CS since he can't sustain it back","Hold Crescendo to interrupt his Bone Skewer (Q) hook or E dash engage","Ward river/tri to track his roams and deny Death From Below resets"],"foe":["Land Bone Skewer (Q) hook to pull you or your ADC into a kill","Hit level 6 and execute low targets with R for gold and resets","Roam with camouflage (W) to snowball a lane elsewhere"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are a skill fight: Pyke is a melee support with no poke shields and low health regen, so you win the sustained trade by chipping him with Hymn of Valor (Q) and Power Chord every time he walks up for a last hit. Keep Aria (W) ready to negate his early Q hook chip. The danger is his Bone Skewer hook — hold a defensive Q slow or W shield for it and never stand in a straight line with your ADC through minions.","mid":"Around level 5-6 Pyke pulls ahead: his ultimate Death From Below executes and resets, and E's Phantom Undertow gives a reliable stun to set up hooks, making his all-in far scarier than your poke pressure. Track his camouflage roams with deep wards and ping his movements. Pre-shield your carry with W and save Crescendo purely to interrupt his hook or R channel rather than for offense.","late":"As items come online the lane tips back to you: your Crescendo is an AoE lockdown that shuts his engage, and your auras and W sustain keep the team above his execute range. Shove and group, deny him isolated picks, and Power Chord Diminuendo to soften his burst. A grouped comp neutralizes his single-pick playstyle.","whys":["Level 1 is even; neither of you has a kill threat and you trade pokes for his positioning.","Level 2 stays a skill matchup as your poke edge is offset by his hook threat.","Level 3 is even; you chip him but he can burst with hook if you misposition.","Levels 4-5 remain skill-based right up until his ult unlocks.","Level 6 favors Pyke as Death From Below execute plus E stun make his all-in lethal.","First item favors Pyke whose R resets and roam pressure snowball harder than your item timing.","2+ items favors Sona as Crescendo and auras peel his engage and neutralize his pick focus."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"rakan","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Rakan","Rakan","Rakan","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Q + Power Chord out-pokes Rakan early since he has to walk into range and his Gleaming Quill (Q) heal only procs off a hit landing on an enemy."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Rakan's Grand Entrance (W) knockup into R The Quickness charm is a lane-flipping all-in; Crescendo can interrupt his W dash or W-in if you time it, but respect his engage range."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Rakan spikes hard with W engage + E shield mobility; your W shield on your ADC blunts his pick, but he dictates when fights start."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your auras and Crescendo counter-engage a diving Rakan; peel his knockup and your carry survives his burst window."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke Rakan with Q before he can W-dash in, denying his Quill heal windows","Pre-shield your ADC with W to survive his Grand Entrance (W) knockup","Ward flanks so he can't E-mobility around for a surprise engage"],"foe":["Land Grand Entrance (W) knockup into Battle Dance (E) to lock you down","Use R The Quickness to charm you and your ADC for a double all-in","Roam and re-engage repeatedly with E shield dashes"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are skill-driven: Rakan is a melee engage support who must close distance, so you win the poke war by landing Hymn of Valor (Q) and Power Chord when he steps up, denying his Gleaming Quill (Q) sustain. Keep Aria (W) up to erase his early chip. The threat is his Grand Entrance knockup — never stand in his dash line and hold a W shield or Q slow for when he commits.","mid":"From level 4 into 6 Rakan takes over: his W knockup into Battle Dance (E) engage, boosted by E's shield and mobility, lets him all-in you or your carry, and level 6 R The Quickness charm makes his dive nearly unstoppable in lane. Ward the flanks, pre-shield with W, and reserve Crescendo to interrupt his W dash-in or peel after he commits. Don't get greedy on poke when his engage is up.","late":"With items the lane swings back to you: Crescendo is a bigger, more reliable AoE stun than his single engage, and your auras plus W sustain keep your team above his burst. Counter-engage his dive, peel the knockup off your carry, and group so his pick attempts fail. Your scaling teamfight presence outlasts his one-shot engage.","whys":["Level 1 is even; Rakan must approach and you match his positioning with poke.","Level 2 stays a skill matchup as your poke edge balances his engage threat.","Level 3 is even; you chip him but his W knockup can flip a trade.","Levels 4-5 favor Rakan as his W-into-E engage and mobility overpower your poke.","Level 6 favors Rakan because R The Quickness charm makes his all-in dominant.","First item favors Rakan whose engage tempo and roam mobility beat your item timing.","2+ items favors Sona as Crescendo and auras counter his dive and peel your carry."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"rell","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Rell","Rell","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Q + Power Chord punishes Rell hard early; she's melee with no poke and her Shattering Strike (Q) only hits if she's already in your face."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Rell's Magnet Storm (R) drags targets together for a team wombo; Crescendo can interrupt her Full Tilt (W) dash engage, but respect her lockdown chain."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Rell spikes with W dash + E stun setup; your W shield eats some of her burst, but her fixed CC chain still dictates fights."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your AoE Crescendo and auras answer Rell's R wombo; peel her dive and keep your carry alive through her lockdown."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke Rell with Q constantly before she W-dashes into range","Pre-shield your ADC with W to survive her Full Tilt (W) crash + Q armor shred","Ward flanks so her W engage can't come from fog"],"foe":["Land Full Tilt (W) dash to crash into you and lock the lane","Chain E stun (with her ADC) into Magnet Storm (R) for a full combo","Dive with her tankiness and armor/MR steal to survive your poke"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are a skill fight: Rell is a melee, immobile-until-W engage tank with zero ranged poke, so you win the sustained lane by chipping her with Hymn of Valor (Q) and Power Chord whenever she approaches for CS or to threaten a crash. Keep Aria (W) ready to heal chip. Her danger is the Full Tilt dash — hold a W shield or Q slow, don't clump with your ADC, and back off when her W is up.","mid":"Around level 5-6 Rell pulls ahead: her W dash-crash engage with E's paired stun gives a long CC chain, and level 6 Magnet Storm turns any grouped fight into a wombo for her side. Her armor/MR steal also makes her hard to burst. Ward the flanks, pre-shield with W, and reserve Crescendo to interrupt her W engage or peel after she commits her lockdown.","late":"With items the lane tips back to you: Crescendo is a reliable AoE stun that answers her engage, and your auras plus W sustain keep the team above her burst-and-CC chain. Counter-engage her dive, peel the crash off your carry, and group so her fixed combo is met with your instant AoE. Your scaling utility outlasts her one-shot engage windows.","whys":["Level 1 is even; Rell can't poke and you match her with positioning.","Level 2 stays a skill matchup as your poke edge offsets her engage threat.","Level 3 is even; you chip her but her W crash can flip a trade.","Levels 4-5 remain skill-based until her CC chain and tankiness fully come online.","Level 6 favors Rell as Magnet Storm plus her W-E lockdown dominate skirmishes.","First item favors Rell whose CC chain and durability beat your item timing.","2+ items favors Sona as Crescendo and auras counter her engage and peel your carry."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"renata","win":["Renata","Renata","Renata","Renata","Skill","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Renata's Handshake (Q) root-toss can pull you or your ADC into a kill early; play back and don't feed her point-and-click engage while she out-ranges your Q."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Renata's Hostile Takeover (R) can force your team to attack each other; your W shield and Crescendo can peel, but her lane pressure is already stronger."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Renata's Bailout (E) shield + attack speed makes her ADC dive lethal; you catch up as your auras and W sustain scale to outheal her poke."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your Crescendo and stacked auras flip fights her Handshake and R try to dictate; peel your carry and neutralize her single-target lockdown."}],"wants":{"you":["Space outside Handshake (Q) range and dodge it since it hard-CCs on toss","Pre-shield your ADC with W against her Bailout-boosted all-ins","Scale to items where your auras and sustain overtake her poke"],"foe":["Land Handshake (Q) to root and fling you into a kill","Use Bailout (E) to turn a losing dive into a kill with the resurrect-ish shield","Flip a fight with Hostile Takeover (R) berserk on your team"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 favor Renata: her Handshake (Q) is a long-range point-and-click root that flings a target, out-threatening your skillshot Hymn of Valor (Q) poke, and Bailout (E) makes her ADC's every trade and dive dangerous. Play respectful spacing, never stand where a Handshake can toss you into her team, and keep Aria (W) up to heal chip. Don't over-commit to poke when her Q is off cooldown.","mid":"Level 5-6 evens out as your kit starts to come online: your W shield + heal can peel her Bailout dives and your Power Chord slows blunt her aggression, though her R Hostile Takeover is a strong teamfight flip you must respect and interrupt with Crescendo when possible. Ward for her Q angles, pre-shield your carry, and stop trading into her when Handshake is up.","late":"With your first item and beyond the lane swings decisively to you (56% win rate reflects it): Crescendo is a hard AoE stun that answers her single-target Handshake, and your auras plus W sustain outheal her poke and keep the team above her burst. Group, peel her engage, and let your scaling utility dominate. Her lane-bully phase fades while your teamfight presence only grows.","whys":["Level 1 favors Renata as her Handshake root out-ranges and out-threatens your poke.","Level 2 favors Renata; her point-and-click Q engage beats your skillshot trades.","Level 3 favors Renata whose Q pull plus Bailout dives keep lane pressure on you.","Levels 4-5 still favor Renata as her all-in tools outpace your early scaling.","Level 6 is even; your W peel and Crescendo start to answer her R and dives.","First item favors Sona as your auras and sustain overtake her poke pressure.","2+ items favors Sona; Crescendo and stacked auras dominate over her single-target kit."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"senna","win":["Senna","Senna","Senna","Senna","Skill","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Senna out-ranges you: her Piercing Darkness (Q) heals her ADC and pokes you at once, and her autos with the long-range passive chip you before your Q lands."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Senna's Dawning Shadow (R) is a global game-changer; in lane play safe and keep W sustain up, since she still out-pokes you into level 6."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Senna scales with soul stacks (range/AD/crit); you catch up as your auras and W heal outlast her poke and Crescendo answers her lane."},{"when":"Late","text":"Your AoE Crescendo and persistent auras win grouped fights; deny Senna's soul farm and peel so her scaling carry threat never fully comes online."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Piercing Darkness (Q) and minimize the free poke-plus-heal she gets","Keep W heal/shield up to negate her long-range auto chip","Scale to items and group where your auras and Crescendo overtake her"],"foe":["Poke you down with Q while healing her ADC in the same cast","Farm souls to snowball range, AD, and crit into a hypercarry","Use Curse of the Black Mist (W) root or camouflage to set up picks"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 favor Senna: Piercing Darkness (Q) both heals her ADC and pokes you in a single cast, and her passive gives extended auto range that chips you before your Hymn of Valor (Q) is even in range. She wins the sustained poke war, so play patient, dodge her Q line, and lean on Aria (W) to undo the chip. Don't walk up to CS into her auto range and never sit in her W mist for the root.","mid":"Level 5-6 evens out as your kit stacks up: your W shield + heal offset her poke, Power Chord slows punish her when she steps up, and Crescendo gives you a real all-in answer, though her global R Dawning Shadow still shifts fights map-wide. Ward for her camouflage roams, pre-shield your carry, and trade back only when her Q is on cooldown.","late":"With your first item onward the lane swings to you: Crescendo is a hard AoE stun that dwarfs her single-target lane pressure, and your auras plus W sustain keep the team above her poke while denying her soul farm. Group and peel — her scaling carry fantasy needs souls and space you take away. Note the near-even 50% win rate: play it tight, but your teamfight utility ultimately edges the grouped stage.","whys":["Level 1 favors Senna as her Q heal-poke and long auto range out-trade you.","Level 2 favors Senna; she pokes and sustains her ADC simultaneously.","Level 3 favors Senna whose range and soul-farm pressure keep you on the back foot.","Levels 4-5 still favor Senna as her poke war edge holds before your spikes.","Level 6 is even; your W peel and Crescendo begin to answer her lane and R.","First item favors Sona as your auras and sustain overtake her poke.","2+ items favors Sona; Crescendo and auras win grouped fights over her single-target kit."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"seraphine","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Seraphine","Seraphine","Seraphine","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Both of you hit the classic bot-lane level-2 breakpoint together; if you get W (Aria of Perseverance) at 2 you can trade into her Q (High Note) poke since your Power Chord and Q (Hymn of Valor) out-DPS her single spell, but her Passive echo makes her all-ins sting so don't overcommit into a fresh Note stack."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R (Encore) is a lane-warping chain-charm that widens the more allies it passes through, so it is a genuine 2v2 game-ender when your ADC is caught next to you; her ult out-ranges and out-impacts your R (Crescendo) tempo, so this is a Seraphine-favoured window unless you can flank the ult angle."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once she completes a stacked Note item plus Moonstone/Dawncore she becomes an oppressive poke-and-shield turret, chunking you with E (Beat Drop) slows into Q while her shields cover the return trade, so she edges the first-item power spike."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your aura utility (Aria movement speed, Diminuendo damage-reduction, Cadence slow) scales your whole team-fight harder than her stationary poke; you dictate engage/disengage tempo with double Crescendo threat, flipping the matchup to Sona."}],"wants":{"you":["Even, skill-based early trades where your Power Chord out-tempos her single-spell casts","Dodging her E (Beat Drop) so her Q and R can't reliably follow up","Reaching 2 items where your aura stacking out-scales her poke"],"foe":["Landing E-into-Q combos to zone you off CS and stack Notes","Catching you and your ADC clustered for a wide Encore charm","Free first-item spike so her shield-and-poke pattern dominates lane"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a genuine skill matchup: you both want the same level-2 timing, and while her Passive echo punishes greedy trades, your Q (Hymn of Valor) plus Power Chord can win a clean short trade if you W-buffer the return poke. Respect that a landed E (Beat Drop) turns her Q and auto into a heavy chunk, so weave through minions and don't stand in her Note-refresh windows.","mid":"From level 4 through 6 Seraphine pulls ahead: her E slow chains into Q for sustained poke your single-target Q can't match, and her shields refund the trades she loses. Her level-6 Encore is the decisive 2v2 tool because it charms wider the more bodies it clips, so keep yourself and your ADC split to deny the multi-charm and hold Crescendo as an interrupt.","late":"On first item her stacked-Note poke and double-shield econ let her out-attrition you, but as your second item lands your aura kit takes over. Diminuendo damage-reduction, Cadence slow, and the movement-speed shove let you close or break any fight on command, and double Crescendo threat means you win the ult trade — the lane and the mid-game team-fights swing to Sona.","whys":["Level 1 is even because neither of you commits and both share the same passive-trade tempo.","Level 2 stays skill-based as your Power Chord and Q can answer her single-spell trade if you time W.","Level 3 remains a coinflip since your sustained aura poke roughly matches her Note-refreshed harass.","At 4-5 her E-into-Q poke chain and shield refunds out-attrition your single-target trades, favouring Seraphine.","Level 6 is Seraphine's because Encore is a wider, longer-range team-charm than your Crescendo in the 2v2.","On first item her stacked poke and double shields make her the stronger laning turret.","By two items your aura utility and double Crescendo out-scale her stationary poke, so Sona takes over."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"soraka","win":["Soraka","Soraka","Soraka","Soraka","Skill","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Soraka out-trades you early because her Q (Starcall) plus E (Equinox) gives her poke-and-slow-and-silence that refunds her own health, while your Q (Hymn of Valor) trades cost you positioning; at the shared level-2 spike she can Q you, self-heal, and win the health war outright."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Neither ult is an engage: her R (Wish) is a global team heal and your R (Crescendo) is an AoE stun, so level 6 is skill-based — it comes down to whether you and your ADC can burst her ADC through the Wish top-up before she reacts."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you complete your first item your aura DPS and Power Chord Staccato pressure let you all-in and pop her before Starcall sustain matters; your kill threat with an aggressive ADC finally out-paces her heal-per-second, so the first-item window swings to Sona."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you fully out-scale a healbot: your Diminuendo/Cadence auras plus double Crescendo win any fight her heals only prolong, and her lack of hard CC means she can't stop your engage — clearly Sona."}],"wants":{"you":["Reaching your first item where all-in burst beats her per-second sustain","Forcing her to spam Q so she can't out-heal a committed all-in","Fights where your Crescendo lands before her Wish top-up"],"foe":["Winning the early poke-and-heal war with Q self-sustain","Landing E (Equinox) to silence and root you out of trades","Dragging lane long with attrition so nobody can be killed"]},"early":"Levels 1 through 4 belong to Soraka. Her Q (Starcall) self-heals on champion hit, so every poke trade she wins she also refunds her own health, and your single Q can't out-attrition that. If she lands E (Equinox) she silences you and can root you when you try to leave, so play for CS, dodge Starcall by weaving minions, and don't try to out-poke a champion who heals off her own harass.","mid":"By level 5-6 it evens out because neither of you has an engage ult — her R (Wish) is a global heal and your Crescendo is an AoE stun. The 2v2 becomes about all-in execution: if you and your ADC can chunk her carry below the Wish threshold and burst through it, you win the exchange; if not, she top-ups and stabilizes. Ward the river and coordinate a Power Chord Staccato slow to lock the kill.","late":"From first item onward the matchup flips to Sona. Your aura DPS and Staccato-empowered Power Chord give you real kill pressure that out-paces her heal-per-second, and Soraka has no CC to stop your engage. Two items in your Diminuendo damage-reduction and double Crescendo decide team-fights outright — she can only delay deaths, not prevent your all-ins.","whys":["Level 1 favours Soraka since her Starcall self-heal wins any opening poke exchange.","Level 2 is Soraka's because Q sustain plus the level-2 spike lets her win the health war.","Level 3 stays Soraka-favoured as her heal-on-hit out-attritions your single-target poke.","At 4-5 her Equinox silence-root and ongoing Q sustain keep her ahead in the poke lane.","Level 6 is even because both ults are non-engage and it comes down to all-in execution.","On first item Sona's all-in burst and Staccato pressure finally out-pace her per-second healing.","By two items Sona out-scales a CC-less healbot with auras and double Crescendo control."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"swain","win":["Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Swain","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Swain bullies the early lane hard: his W (Vision of Empire) zones your CS and his E (Nevermove) is a delayed root that, if it lands, lets his Q (Death's Hand) shred you and pull a Soul Fragment; at the level-2 spike a landed E-into-Q can chunk you for a third of your bar, so he owns the opening."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R (Demonic Ascension) turns him into a lane-drain monster — every tick heals him and builds toward Demonflare, so a 2v2 all-in around 6 into an ulted Swain usually feeds him a double; this is firmly his window and you should disengage rather than trade."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Liandry's/Rylai's plus his Passive Soul Fragment stacks, Swain becomes a durable long-range poke bruiser who out-sustains and out-ranges your trades, so the first-item window still belongs to him."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your aura mobility and double Crescendo let you dodge his telegraphed E and disengage his ult drain, and your ADC out-scales an immobile mage — the fight tempo finally flips to Sona."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestepping his E (Nevermove) so his Q and all-in never connect","Staying at max range to deny Soul Fragment poke stacks","Reaching two items where mobility and disengage beat his immobility"],"foe":["Landing delayed E roots to chain into Q and W zoning","Ulting into a 2v2 all-in to drain-heal through your damage","Free Soul Fragment stacks to snowball his durability and range"]},"early":"Levels 1 through 4 are rough for you. Swain's W zones the wave from a screen away, and his real threat is E (Nevermove): the delayed twin-snare will root you and your ADC if you stand still, letting him land a full Q (Death's Hand) shred and harvest a Soul Fragment for extra durability. Hug the minion line, juke the E's travel time, and give up contested CS rather than eating a snare — his early kill pressure off one landed root is enormous.","mid":"Through level 6 he stays ahead. His poke keeps stacking Fragments into more health, and his level-6 R (Demonic Ascension) is a sustained drain that heals him for every champion tick and charges Demonflare. Do not 2v2 all-in into an ulted Swain — his lifesteal-through-damage will win a prolonged fight and can snowball a double. Hold Crescendo purely to peel his E-engage and disengage, and let him waste ult uptime.","late":"On first item his Liandry's/Rylai's plus Fragment stacks make him a tanky long-range nuisance, so keep respecting range. But two items in the matchup swings to Sona: your Aria movement speed and double Crescendo let you cleanly dodge the telegraphed E and break his drain, and your hyper-scaling ADC out-damages an immobile mage in extended fights. Convert the mid-game peel into out-scaling him.","whys":["Level 1 is Swain's as his W zoning and E threat control the lane from range.","Level 2 favours Swain because a landed E-into-Q at the spike chunks you hard.","Level 3 stays Swain's as Soul Fragment poke keeps building his durability.","At 4-5 his range and Fragment-stacked health keep out-trading your poke.","Level 6 is Swain's because his ult drain wins any 2v2 all-in around it.","On first item his Liandry's/Rylai's plus Fragments make him a durable long-range bully.","By two items Sona's mobility, disengage, and scaling ADC finally flip the fight."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"tahmkench","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Tahm Kench","Tahm Kench","Tahm Kench","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Early it's a skill matchup: Tahm's Q (Tongue Lash) is a slow-and-stun-on-triple-stack poke, but your Q (Hymn of Valor) plus Power Chord out-DPS his single tongue if you dodge it; at the level-2 spike, respect that a landed Q into an all-in can set up his kill threat, but a clean juke keeps trades even."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R (Abyssal Dive) is a gap-close engage and his W (Devour) can eat his own ADC to save it or spit yours, so the 2v2 all-in around 6 favours Tahm — his pick-and-peel toolkit around your team beats your reactive Crescendo, making it his window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With his passive Grey Health regen and first tank item, Tahm shrugs off your poke and his Q triple-stack stun sets up repeatable all-ins, so the durable-engage first-item spike belongs to Tahm Kench."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your Diminuendo damage-reduction and double Crescendo let you peel his Q-stun engage and Devour picks, and your out-scaling aura DPS wins the team-fight tempo — the matchup flips to Sona."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodging his Q (Tongue Lash) so he never builds the triple-stack stun","Even skill-trades early where Power Chord out-tempos his single tongue","Reaching two items where Diminuendo and Crescendo peel his engage"],"foe":["Landing three Q stacks to stun and open an all-in","Using R (Abyssal Dive) to dive your backline in the 2v2","Devouring his ADC to negate your burst then re-engaging"]},"early":"Levels 1 through 3 are a genuine skill matchup. Tahm's main lane tool is Q (Tongue Lash), a slow that stuns on the third stack, so the whole early game is about never eating three tongues in a row — weave minions and punish the wind-up. Your Q plus Power Chord out-damage his single-spell poke, so if you sidestep the tongue you win the short trades; if you get lazy and take stacks, his all-in kill pressure is real.","mid":"From level 4 through 6 Tahm edges ahead. His Grey Health passive lets him tank your poke and heal it off, his Q triple-stack repeatedly threatens a stun-opened all-in, and at 6 his R (Abyssal Dive) gap-closes onto your ADC while W (Devour) can save his own carry from your burst. Hold Crescendo to interrupt his dive rather than for offense, ward the flanks his ult can come from, and don't 2v2 into his full engage-and-peel kit.","late":"On first item his tankiness and Q-stun engage keep him ahead in lane. But two items in the matchup swings to Sona: your Diminuendo damage-reduction and double Crescendo peel his stun-engage and Devour picks, while your aura DPS and out-scaling ADC win extended team-fights that his single-target save-tool can't carry. Turn the mid-game peel into a scaling lead.","whys":["Level 1 is even as neither commits and trades stay skill-based.","Level 2 stays skill-based since Power Chord out-tempos his single Q if you dodge.","Level 3 remains a coinflip decided by whether he lands his triple-stack stun.","At 4-5 his Grey Health tankiness and Q-stun all-in threat pull him ahead.","Level 6 is Tahm's because his R dive plus Devour peel win the 2v2 all-in.","On first item his tank item and repeatable stun engage keep him dominant.","By two items Sona's Diminuendo, Crescendo peel, and scaling flip the fight."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"taric","win":["Taric","Taric","Taric","Taric","Taric","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Taric wins the early bully war: his Q (Starlight's Touch) heals off stacked charges while his empowered auto and E (Dazzle) stun threaten a hard all-in; at the level-2 spike his sustain plus stun kill-setup outclasses your poke, so he owns the opening."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R (Cosmic Radiance) makes him and his ADC invulnerable after a short delay, completely negating your Crescendo all-in and turning any 2v2 he initiates into a free trade — clearly Taric's window, do not commit into an up ult."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With his first item and Bravado auto-resets plus Q-heal sustain, Taric is a durable stun-and-heal engage support that out-lanes your poke, so the first-item spike still belongs to Taric."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in your aura DPS, Diminuendo, and double Crescendo out-tempo his cooldown-gated engage, and your ADC out-scales his short-range kit — the fight finally flips to Sona once his ult is on cooldown."}],"wants":{"you":["Baiting or tracking his R (Cosmic Radiance) cooldown before you commit","Dodging his E (Dazzle) stun line to deny the all-in setup","Reaching two items where your aura DPS beats his cooldown-gated engage"],"foe":["Stacking Q charges to out-sustain your early poke","Landing E (Dazzle) through minions to stun-open a kill","Ulting invulnerable to negate your Crescendo and win the 2v2"]},"early":"Levels 1 through 5 are Taric's, and the sub-48% win rate shows it — he simply out-bullies you. His Q (Starlight's Touch) heals off stacked charges so he sustains through your poke, his Bravado empowered autos hurt, and his E (Dazzle) is a stun that sets up an all-in through the minion wave. Play safe, dodge the Dazzle line, farm from range, and don't try to win an early poke war against a champion who heals and stuns better than you trade.","mid":"Through level 6 he stays ahead because his R (Cosmic Radiance) grants delayed invulnerability to him and his ADC, hard-countering your Crescendo engage — if you flip an all-in into an up ult, your damage simply zeroes out and he punishes you. Track his ult cooldown obsessively, ward for his E-engage angle, hold Crescendo to peel rather than initiate, and only fight when his R is down.","late":"The lane favours Taric on first item too, as Bravado resets plus Q sustain keep him a durable stun-engage support. But two items in the matchup finally swings to Sona: your aura DPS, Diminuendo damage-reduction, and double Crescendo out-tempo his cooldown-gated engage, and your ADC out-scales his short-range toolkit. Play the early defensively, deny snowball, and cash in your scaling once his ult windows open up.","whys":["Level 1 is Taric's as his Q sustain and empowered autos out-bully your poke.","Level 2 favours Taric because his heal plus E stun win the all-in at the spike.","Level 3 stays Taric's with Q-charge sustain out-attritioning your trades.","At 4-5 his Dazzle stun and heal keep him dominant in the poke lane.","Level 6 is Taric's because Cosmic Radiance invulnerability negates your Crescendo.","On first item his Bravado resets and Q sustain keep the durable engage ahead.","By two items Sona's aura DPS and double Crescendo out-scale his cooldown-gated kit."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"thresh","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Thresh","Thresh","Thresh","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Early it's skill-based: Thresh has no early sustain and relies entirely on landing Q (Death Sentence), so if you respect the hook and juke behind minions your Q plus Power Chord out-poke him; at the level-2 spike a missed hook leaves him vulnerable, but a landed one can chain his E flay into a kill, so it lives and dies on his hook accuracy."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His R (The Box) is a multi-wall slow-and-damage cage that traps your all-in or disengage, and combined with a hook it makes the 2v2 around 6 a hard pick threat against you and your ADC — Thresh's window, hold Crescendo to interrupt rather than fight into the Box."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With his Lantern (W) save utility, flay peel, and hook range on first item, Thresh's pick-and-peel package out-tempos your poke; every landed hook is a kill setup while his Lantern erases your engage, so the first-item spike is his."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in, your Diminuendo and double Crescendo let you dodge and punish his single telegraphed hook, and your aura DPS wins fights that his utility only prolongs — once he whiffs a hook you out-scale him, flipping to Sona."}],"wants":{"you":["Juking his Q (Death Sentence) behind minions so his whole combo is dead","Even skill-trades early where Power Chord out-pokes a sustain-less Thresh","Reaching two items where your aura DPS punishes his missed hooks"],"foe":["Landing Q hooks to chain E (Flay) into a kill setup","Using R (The Box) to cage your all-in or disengage in the 2v2","Lantern (W) saves that negate your Crescendo pick attempts"]},"early":"Levels 1 through 3 are a genuine skill matchup. Thresh has no innate sustain and his entire threat funnels through Q (Death Sentence), so the lane is a hook-dodging contest — stand behind your minions, watch his wind-up, and every whiffed hook is a free window where your Q and Power Chord out-poke him. If you get lazy and eat a hook, his E (Flay) reposition into an ADC all-in can convert it to a kill, so discipline decides the early.","mid":"From level 4 through 6 Thresh edges ahead. His hook range and Flay peel give him repeatable pick threat, his Lantern (W) can pull an over-extended ADC out of your Crescendo, and at 6 his R (The Box) walls off your all-in or your escape, making the 2v2 a coinflip you'd rather not take. Ward the flanks his hooks come from, hold Crescendo to interrupt his engage instead of initiating, and only commit when his Q is on cooldown.","late":"On first item his pick-and-peel package keeps him ahead — a landed hook is a kill, and Lantern erases your picks. But two items in the matchup swings to Sona: your Diminuendo damage-reduction and double Crescendo let you dodge and immediately punish his single telegraphed hook, while your aura DPS wins extended fights his utility only stalls. Deny early hooks, survive the mid-game, and out-scale a champion who's only as strong as his last Q.","whys":["Level 1 is even as a sustain-less Thresh must land a hook while you poke safely.","Level 2 stays skill-based since a missed Q leaves him open to your Power Chord poke.","Level 3 remains a coinflip decided purely by his hook accuracy.","At 4-5 his repeatable hook-and-flay pick threat and Lantern peel pull him ahead.","Level 6 is Thresh's because The Box plus a hook makes the 2v2 a hard pick on you.","On first item his pick-and-peel utility out-tempos your poke every landed hook.","By two items Sona's Diminuendo and double Crescendo punish his missed hooks and out-scale him."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"velkoz","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Vel'Koz","Vel'Koz","Vel'Koz","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Both of you spike at 2, but it's a wash: you get Power Chord plus a heal-shield off your second Aria, while Vel'Koz gets Q (Tectonic Disruption) into E (Void Rift) for a knock-up combo. Hold your ADC back from the line his Q splits into and answer his poke with Aria of Perseverance sustain rather than trying to trade Hymn Q back into his longer range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Vel'Koz's ult, Life Form Disintegration Ray, is the real threat spike here — if you or your ADC get chained by his W-Q-E true-damage combo he can channel a full beam and delete you. Your Crescendo can interrupt that channel, but only if you're positioned to flank; used reactively from range it saves the ADC. This window is his, so respect the all-in he threatens once his passive Deconstruction stacks are up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"On your first completed item (Moonstone or Dawncore) his poke war peaks: Vel'Koz has Blackfire Torch or Ludens online and each Q-E combo chunks harder than your Aria heals. Keep moving between his Q lines, wave-clear from max range, and don't facecheck brush he can pre-charge his poke into."},{"when":"Late","text":"Teamfights flip to you: Sona's auras (Aria damage, Sole Sona movespeed) plus a game-ending Crescendo on a clumped team out-value Vel'Koz's single-target beam. In a coordinated 5v5 your ult catches him before he can free-cast his ray, and your ADC-enabling shields win the fight — this is your phase."}],"wants":{"you":["Trades that force his cooldowns then punish the ~7s downtime on his Q-E poke combo","Sidestepping his split Q so it only hits one target for reduced damage","Late 5v5s where your Crescendo hits multiple and your auras enable your carry"],"foe":["Long, static poke wars where his Q-E-W outranges your Aria heal","Landing his full W-Q-E true-damage combo to burst you or your ADC","A level-6 all-in where his ult finishes a target you already chunked"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are even skill checks: Vel'Koz outranges your Aria Q but his mana and long cooldowns mean he can't poke forever, and your sustain refills what he chips. Trade back only when his Q or E is down, keep your ADC out of the brush he pre-aims into, and hold Power Chord for a punish rather than wasting it into shove.","mid":"From 4 through 6 the poke war tilts to Vel'Koz — his combo comes online, his passive Deconstruction adds true damage, and at 6 his Life Form Disintegration Ray threatens a kill if you clump. Ward his flanks, dodge the Q lines, and keep Crescendo up as your interrupt for his channel rather than opening with it.","late":"Once items and levels stack, Sona takes over: your auras and a multi-target Crescendo win 5v5s outright, and your heal-shield keeps your carry alive through his single beam. Group, force fights on your terms, and let his poke matter less as everyone's health pool grows.","whys":["Level 1 is even — his range edges poke but your sustain and Power Chord keep it a skill trade.","Level 2 is a coin-flip spike: your heal-shield answers his Q-E knock-up combo evenly.","Level 3 stays even as his mana costs cap his poke and your Aria refills the chip.","Levels 4-5 favour Vel'Koz — his full combo and passive true damage outrange your heal.","Level 6 is his: Life Form Disintegration Ray threatens to delete a clumped target.","At first item his poke peaks with Ludens/Blackfire while your sustain lags his burst.","At 2+ items Sona wins — multi-target Crescendo and auras out-value his single beam."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"xerath","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Xerath","Xerath","Xerath","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"You both come online at 2, and it's even: your second Aria gives you a heal-shield plus Power Chord, while Xerath gets Q (Arcanopulse) plus W (Eye of Destruction) for a slow-into-poke chain. Stand off his charged Q's max range, sustain the chip with Aria, and don't let him zone your ADC off the wave with the AoE slow field."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Xerath's ult, Rite of the Ancients, turns his lane into a global artillery threat — three long-range shots that can snipe you or your ADC from screens away, especially after his W slow lands. His window, not yours: pre-position behind minions, spread from your ADC so one shot can't hit both, and hold Crescendo to punish if he steps up to secure a kill."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Blackfire Torch or Ludens up, Xerath's charged Q outranges everything you have and each landed W-Q chunks harder than Aria of Perseverance can heal back. This is the peak of his poke dominance — clear from distance, weave behind terrain, and avoid the brush he pre-charges Q into."},{"when":"Late","text":"The game swings to Sona: in a grouped 5v5 your auras and a clean Crescendo on his backline win the fight before his artillery matters, and your shields keep your carry topped through his shots. Force fights in tight terrain where he can't free-cast, and this becomes your phase."}],"wants":{"you":["Short, ended trades that force his Q then punish its long cast and cooldown","Splitting from your ADC so a single W-Q can't tag both of you","Late grouped fights where Crescendo and your auras out-value his artillery"],"foe":["Open-lane poke where his charged Q and W slow outrange your Aria heal","Landing W to slow, then guaranteeing the Q and ult snipe","Level-6 picks where Rite of the Ancients finishes a poked-down target"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are an even skill matchup: Xerath's charged Q outranges your Aria Q, but the long cast time lets you sidestep it, and your sustain refills the chip he lands. Trade back only inside his Q downtime, keep your ADC out of his W slow field, and don't waste Power Chord into a bad angle.","mid":"From 4 through 6 the poke war goes to Xerath — his mana and range let him chip endlessly, his W sets up guaranteed Q's, and at 6 Rite of the Ancients threatens long-range picks on anyone caught out. Ward his firing angles, spread from your ADC, and treat Crescendo as your step-up punish rather than an opener.","late":"Once items stack Sona takes over: grouped 5v5s reward your multi-target Crescendo and constant auras while your heal-shield sustains your carry through his snipes. Fight in tight terrain, close the gap fast, and his artillery stops mattering.","whys":["Level 1 is even — his range pokes but the slow cast lets you dodge and out-sustain it.","Level 2 is an even spike: your heal-shield and Power Chord answer his Q-W chain.","Level 3 stays even as mana costs cap his poke and Aria refills the chip.","Levels 4-5 favour Xerath — his W-into-Q poke outranges and out-damages your heal.","Level 6 is his: Rite of the Ancients snipes clumped or poked-down targets from range.","At first item his charged Q and Ludens burst outpace your Aria sustain.","At 2+ items Sona wins — grouped Crescendo and auras out-value his single-target snipes."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"yuumi","win":["Sona","Sona","Sona","Sona","Sona","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"You spike hard at 2 and Yuumi doesn't: your second Aria stacks Power Chord and gives a heal-shield, so you can walk up and land an empowered auto plus Hymn Q poke on an attached Yuumi's ADC. Yuumi attached to her carry has no way to answer your damage aura — she can only heal reactively, so force the trade whenever her ADC steps to last-hit."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Crescendo is a genuine kill threat here; Yuumi's ult (Final Chapter) is waves of skillshots that are easy to walk out of and can't peel a hard engage. If your ADC has a follow-up, flank and land Crescendo on her carry — attached, Yuumi can't body-block or CC you off. This window is clearly yours."},{"when":"1st item","text":"On Moonstone or Dawncore your poke-and-sustain snowballs: your Aria out-heals Yuumi's early sustain while adding damage she has none of. Keep chipping the ADC every time they walk up, deny her the attach-heal value, and press your health lead into dives."},{"when":"Late","text":"Sona stays ahead: your auras (damage, movespeed, shield) enable a full 5v5 while Yuumi is purely reactive glued to one carry. A game-ending Crescendo on their grouped team wins fights outright, and your peel keeps your own carry alive better than her heals keep theirs."}],"wants":{"you":["Walking up to poke the ADC every time Yuumi detaches or her carry last-hits","Landing Crescendo on the enemy carry — attached, Yuumi can't peel it","Snowballing an early health lead into dives before her scaling comes online"],"foe":["A passive lane where she out-sustains your poke by permanently attaching","Free scaling to 2+ items where her attached healing and MS become oppressive","Picking off your ADC when you're out of position and can't return the heal"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are yours: Yuumi attached to her ADC can only react with heals while you bring both sustain and a damage aura, so every time her carry steps to CS you punish with an empowered auto and Hymn Q. Zone the melee-range brush, keep Power Chord ready, and build a health lead early before she gets rolling.","mid":"From 3 through 6 you keep pressing — your poke out-trades her passive attach-healing, and at 6 Crescendo threatens a kill her Final Chapter can't stop. Ward the river for her jungler since she offers zero lane pressure, coordinate an all-in with your ADC on her carry, and force fights while you're ahead.","late":"With items Sona still leads: your auras enable the whole team in 5v5 and a clean Crescendo on their group wins the fight, while Yuumi remains locked reactively to one carry. Group, peel your own carry, and close the game before her scaling heals snowball out of control.","whys":["Level 1 is yours — you bring damage plus sustain while attached Yuumi only reacts.","Level 2 is your spike: Power Chord and a heal-shield let you win the walk-up trade.","Level 3 stays yours as your poke out-trades her passive attach-healing.","Levels 4-5 favour you — a health lead and your aura pressure her reactive kit can't match.","Level 6 is yours: Crescendo threatens a kill her escapable Final Chapter can't peel.","At first item your Aria sustain-plus-damage snowballs over her early healing.","At 2+ items Sona's team-wide auras and Crescendo out-value her single-carry reactivity."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"zilean","win":["Zilean","Zilean","Zilean","Zilean","Skill","Sona","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Zilean spikes harder than you here: with two bombs he can double-Q for a stun (Q into E-refreshed Q) that chains you or your ADC, and his poke range beats your Aria. Your level-2 heal-shield is answer-only — respect his double-bomb window, keep your ADC back from the AoE, and don't step up for a Power Chord trade into a pending stun."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is the even skill window: Zilean's ult (Chronoshift) revives a target, which blunts your all-in but doesn't add lane pressure, while your Crescendo can hard-engage or peel. If you can burst a target below the revive and follow up, or CC him off the Chronoshift value, the fight is winnable — outplay decides it rather than raw kit."},{"when":"1st item","text":"On your first item (Moonstone/Dawncore) the lane starts flipping to you: Zilean's bomb poke stays dangerous but your sustain-and-aura package out-scales his static kit, and Chronoshift only ever saves one target once per fight. Trade in his double-bomb downtime and start pressing your health advantage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Sona wins the long game: your team-wide auras and a multi-target Crescendo outvalue Zilean's single-target revive and speed buffs. In 5v5 he can save one ally while your ult swings the whole fight — this phase is yours, so group and force teamfights."}],"wants":{"you":["Trading inside his double-bomb cooldown when the stun isn't up","Late 5v5s where Crescendo hits multiple and your auras beat his single revive","Pressing a health lead once your first item out-scales his static poke"],"foe":["Early lane where his bomb poke outranges your Aria and double-Q stuns","Zoning your ADC off the wave with AoE bombs and E speed plays","Using Chronoshift to nullify your all-in and swing an even 6 fight"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Zilean: his bomb poke outranges your Aria Q, and the double-Q stun (using E to reset his bomb) can lock you or your ADC for a punish you can only heal after. Play back, soak the chip with Aria of Perseverance, keep your carry out of the AoE, and don't over-extend for a Power Chord into a pending stun.","mid":"Level 5 evens out and 6 is a skill fight — Chronoshift protects one target but adds no poke, while your Crescendo threatens engage or peel. Look to trade in his bomb downtime, ward for the jungler since his stun makes ganks lethal, and coordinate an all-in that burns through or plays around the revive.","late":"Once items land Sona takes over: your auras enable the whole team and a grouped Crescendo out-values his single-target revive and speed buffs. Force 5v5s, press your health lead from the item spike, and let his static kit fall behind your scaling.","whys":["Level 1 favours Zilean — his bomb poke outranges your Aria from the first trade.","Level 2 is his: the double-bomb stun threatens a lock-and-punish you can only heal after.","Level 3 stays Zilean's as his poke range keeps chipping past your sustain.","Levels 4-5... level 4 is still his with bomb poke zoning your ADC off the wave.","Level 6 is an even skill fight — Chronoshift saves one but adds no lane pressure vs your Crescendo.","At first item Sona flips it — your sustain-and-aura package out-scales his static poke.","At 2+ items Sona wins: grouped Crescendo and auras out-value his single revive."]},
  {"a":"sona_sup","b":"zyra","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Zyra","Zyra","Zyra","Sona"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 2","text":"Both spike at 2 and it's even: your second Aria stacks Power Chord and gives a heal-shield, while Zyra gets Q (Deadly Spines) plus E (Grasping Roots) for a root-into-seeded-plant combo. Don't step onto her seeds — her plants amplify every ability — and answer the poke with Aria sustain rather than trading Hymn Q into her longer, plant-boosted range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Zyra's ult, Stranglethorn, is a delayed AoE knock-up that, comboed with her E root and a plant field, can chain-CC and burst you or your ADC in one window. This is her spike — hold Crescendo to interrupt her follow-up or peel the engage, spread from your ADC so the ult doesn't catch both, and don't clump on her seeds when Stranglethorn is up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Blackfire Torch or Liandry's online, Zyra's plant-boosted poke chunks harder than Aria of Perseverance heals back, and her E root sets up guaranteed damage. This is the peak of her lane pressure — clear from range, sidestep her Q lines, and never facecheck brush she can pre-seed."},{"when":"Late","text":"Sona pulls ahead: your team-wide auras and a clean Crescendo on their grouped team out-value Zyra's zone-control-plus-plants once fights spread across a full 5v5. Your heal-shield sustains your carry through her DoT, and your ult swings the fight — this phase is yours."}],"wants":{"you":["Trading in the downtime after her E root and plant seeds are spent","Splitting from your ADC so Stranglethorn and her E can't chain both","Late 5v5s where Crescendo and your auras beat her single zone of plants"],"foe":["Poke wars where her plant-amplified Q-E outranges your Aria heal","Landing E root to guarantee plant damage and set up her all-in","Level-6 Stranglethorn comboed with root and plants to burst a clumped target"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are an even skill matchup: Zyra's plant-boosted Q outranges your Aria Q, but her plants and mana are finite, so your sustain refills the chip between her combos. Trade back only when her E root and seeds are down, keep your ADC off her plant fields, and hold Power Chord for a clean punish rather than feeding it into shove.","mid":"From 4 through 6 the lane tilts to Zyra — her plant poke ramps, her E root guarantees follow-up, and at 6 Stranglethorn threatens a chain-CC burst on a clumped bot lane. Ward her flanks, spread from your ADC, dodge the Q lines, and keep Crescendo as your interrupt for her ult combo rather than opening with it.","late":"Once items and levels stack Sona takes over: grouped 5v5s reward your multi-target Crescendo and constant auras while your heal-shield out-sustains her DoT on your carry. Fight where her plants can't zone you, close the gap, and her single AoE stops out-valuing your team-wide impact.","whys":["Level 1 is even — her plant range pokes but your sustain refills between finite combos.","Level 2 is an even spike: your heal-shield and Power Chord answer her Q-E plant combo.","Level 3 stays even as her mana and plant cooldowns cap the poke your Aria heals.","Levels 4-5 favour Zyra — her plant-boosted poke and E root outrange and out-damage your heal.","Level 6 is hers: Stranglethorn plus root and plants chain-CC and burst a clumped target.","At first item her Liandry's-plant poke chunks past your Aria sustain.","At 2+ items Sona wins — grouped Crescendo and auras out-value her single plant zone."]}
